section.def:
instrument
                (文書) means any document having legal effect
            except a will;

mortgage
                (按揭) means a security over land for securing
            money or money’s worth;

mortgagee
                (承按人) includes any person claiming under a
            mortgagee;

mortgagor
                (按揭人) includes any person claiming under a
            mortgagor;

paragraph.content:
affect any interest validly created before the
                commencement*
                of this section;

the equitable interest under that right shall become a legal estate in that
                    land as if held under a Government lease issued in accordance with that right;
                        and (Amended 31 of 1988 s. 7)

the equitable interest under that right shall become a legal estate in that
                    land as if held under a Government lease issued in accordance with that right;
                    and

any definition used in, or, by this section, incorporated into, that instrument
                shall extend to the grammatical variations and cognate expressions of the word or
                expression defined;

section.def:
law (法律、法例、法) means any
            law for the time being in force in, having legislative effect in, extending to or
            applicable to Hong Kong;

New
                Kowloon (新九龍) means the area specified in
            the Fifth Schedule to the Interpretation and General Clauses Ordinance (Cap. 1);

occupy (佔用) includes use, inhabit, be in possession of or enjoy
            the land to which the word relates otherwise than as a mere servant or for the mere
            purpose of the care, custody or charge thereof;

registered
                (註冊), in relation to a document, means registered
            under any law applicable to the registration of that document;

sign (簽名、簽署) includes, in
            the case of a person unable to write, the affixing or making of his seal, mark,
            thumbprint or chop;

subsection.def:
building
                    (建築物) has the same meaning as in the
                Buildings Ordinance (Cap. 123);

def.continued:
and in respect of which any relevant certificate of compliance has been
                    issued or is taken to have been issued, or the requisite consent has been
                    obtained from the Director of Lands;

subsection.def:
development
                    (發展項目) means a development involving the
                construction of a new building;

paragraph.content:
in an assignment to a purchaser for valuable consideration, the covenants,
                    by a person who is expressed to assign as beneficial owner, mentioned in Part II
                    of the First Schedule;

in an assignment by way of voluntary disposition, the covenant, by a person
                    who is expressed to assign as donor, mentioned in Part III of the First
                        Schedule;

to assign to the purchaser the mortgagor’s estate in that land, subject to
                    any other mortgage having priority to the mortgage under which the sale is made;
                    and

paragraph.def:
lessee
                        (承租人) includes an original or derivative
                    under-lessee, and the persons deriving title under a lessee;

lessor
                        (批租人) includes an original or derivative
                    under-lessor, and the persons deriving title under a lessor;

paragraph.content:
to execute a legal charge over that land in favour of the mortgagee in such
                    form and containing such covenants and provisions as the mortgagee may require;
                    and
